-- Depression Costing Australian Economy $709 Million a Year, Review Reports
-- B y   E l i s a b e t h   B e h r m a n n
-- 2010-10-05T20:19:14Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-05/depression-costing-australian-economy-709-million-a-year-review-reports.html
Depression as a result of job strain
is costing the Australian economy A$730 million a year, the
Australian Financial Review reported, citing a study by
Melbourne Associate Professor Anthony LaMontagne. In Australia,
some 1.5 million workers have had depression as a result of a
poor working environment, according to the report.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Elisabeth Behrmann in Sydney at 
 ebehrmann1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
